Do people agree with my comments/proposals?<br>
<br>
I play a lvl 57 Magician on Tunare and am working on the magician Epic.<br>
<br>
I finally have 28 of the 30 pieces required (including sub quests and temple ro focus item quests)after over a YEAR of effort. It's really been a time sink but for the most part I've enjoyed the anticipation of finally seeing that last &quot;You've gained experience&quot; message from the Master of Elements in the Plane of Air and being able to scribe a spell long missing from my book. It's also been a great guide to the game as I've been forced to travel all over the place and learn new zones or long forgotten ones. Friends have helped and sometimes I've spent so much time camping elusive mobs with elusive drops when I could solo. The quest makes for a lot of conversation with other mages and these are mostly all good things.<br>
<br>
My only question (gripe if you will) is that there are mobs which are intensely contested over, with one in particular that is beyond reasonable (and I have a lot of patience); this one being the elusive Magi Phasta in Hate.<br>
<br>
Let me describe my personal experiences so far:<br>
<br>
1.) I've been on 14 Hate raids &amp; have all my Apothic armor. I even saw a Rainments of the Chosen drop and won the random on it.<br>
2.) I've logged over 60 hours in that zone just looking for the staff &amp; I've never once SEEN Magi Phasta (never mind thinking about the chance to loot him). I spent the last 4 consecutive days straight (Sunday all day, Monday night, Tuesday night, Wednesday night) on every Hate raid I could and still didn't see him.<br>
3.) I heard he spawned once while I was in the zone on a raid a while ago, but the raid had been going on for a while and it was late so we folded and we never got to see him.<br>
4.) There were a lot of minis up on one raid I went to and the Fire staff dropped. This was a semi-open raid. The server ezboard raid post said that the Earth staff was spoken for IF a particular mage showed up; since that mage wasn't there I went on the raid. After the shout from the leader of the group who got the exp from Mistress of Scorn that a mage staff dropped, the raid leader got excited and due to greed and ignorance told the group leader to loot the staff (i.e. intending to MQ it for the mage who wasn't even there) so the group leader promptly did. A No Drop fire pet focus item staff was thus burned. I would have enjoyed a random on that but I ended up very angry and frustrated.<br>
5.) The only other time I saw a fire staff drop in Hate (on a semi-open raid I went on to try to get all my Apothic on for the hope that maybe just maybe someday on some raid seniority might count for something), the raid leader gifted it to a mage in his guild who was the one slated to get the Earth staff should it drop. The reasoning there was that it was at the end of the raid and Magi wasn't up so because that mage didn't get what she came for that day she might as well get the reward of the other mage staff. I was also upset at that - so much for &quot;semi-open&quot; that day.<br>
6.) Here's a common quote from a reservation for the Plane on the Tunare server board regarding epic drops in Hate on a semi open raid, &quot;Please note: Certain epic bits may be already spoken for, such as the ranger stones and the magi epic staff depending on if guildmates/friends have already gotten them or not. If that's the only reason you are looking to attend, you may well be disappointed.&quot; A lot of raids say this and I don't bother anymore to attend them anymore. Other &quot;open&quot; raids say that the leader will decide the epic drops for whatever that means.<br>
7.) I have resources of my own (I know the counter argument to some of the points above) and could host my own raid. I have a few lvl 60 cleric friends, a high lvl enchanter friend, a high lvl monk friend that's pulled hate a bazillion times, a bunch of driud friends, a couple wizard friends who could port up, a bunch of warriors, etc and it wouldn't be too much trouble to reserve the plane a couple weeks in advance and rock the zone. The only trouble is, based on my experience, what are the odds that after being on 14 Hate raids and logging 60 hours in Hate without seeing Magi drop, that I can expect Magi to be there when I go? Do you HONESTLY expect my friends and guildmates to reserve ALL their free time on some stupid repetative task like this and go to Hate over and over and over and over again for nothing? Not one of them would be interested in that and I'm not going to bother asking them to do that.<br>
8.) There do exist large powerful guilds on the server that are capable of and have many characters that need to go to hate to get epic pieces and want to (unlike my smaller guild of people who haven't done a lot with higher level characters or are as far into their epics). The guilds have people who port to hate with a tracker or someone who can navigate the zone and see what mobs are up. If the right mob is up, they will pull it and to hell with the scheduled open raid later that day.<br>
9.) When I do go up on an open raid (there's not going to be another open or semi-open raid on my server for the next 4 days which is how I have time to write this now) and IF on the offchance Magi spawns just before or during the raid and IF there's time left to pull him, I will find myself randoming between myself and other mages I've become friends with. This hurts me emotionally either way it turns out. If I win, I'd be very happy to consider myself done with my epic and go on to other things (a lot left to do) but I'd also be distraught that a friend of mine or another mage I don't know didn't win and might be resentful or sad and frustrated.<br>
10.) It's also possible that the Earth staff can be looted for Multiquest and sold. Closed raids without mages or if the epic will just looted leave the possibility of someone making 50-150k pp on this item. I don't support that but it happens.<br>
11.) I know two mages who have been to Hate more than 50 times and still don't have the item, but on the other hand I know of two more that have been on only a dozen and were able to get the staff. That doesn't seem balanced. I also know of mages who haven't started the epic quest due to the difficulty of getting the staff.<br>
<br>
This whole situation brought about by the rarity of a mob and his drop has caused a lot of people to go to extremes and I've seen some of it up there and I've mentioned a couple examples. There's a lot of GREED and I'm very upset and unhappy about it.<br>
<br>
The situation is intolerable and unacceptable. There are other solutions that don't necessarily go against the original difficulty or intention of the epic quests. I know it's a hard quest, it's a status symbol, and it's for a very good item so it's supposed to be hard; it shouldn't, however, be a cause of contention between people or nearly impossible considering how many people want the item and what lengths they could go to to reduce the grief associated with it.<br>
<br>
Does Verant have any intentions in the future of stopping people from being able to Multiquest items for quests? This would help very very much, considering that if this was the case only people who were IN the zone of the right class could use the item. It isn't the best solution as far as I'm concerned though because there would still be lots of closed or &quot;semi-open&quot; raids where the item would be spoken for in advance before the raid even started.<br>
<br>
Consider other solutions, here's a few examples:<br>
1.) Add a mob to the Zone deep on the second floor that isn't aggro who is on some kind of anti-forsaken revenant faction that is raised only after spending so much time in Hate fighting forsaken revenants (a mob in Hate who hates other mobs imagine that LOL). There could be a quest where a mage could receive an Earth Staff that is being held by this mob after things that drop on forsaken revenants are turned in. Right now basically that's Apothic armor. This kind of quest requires 6 or 7 hate raids (or more) to accumulate a set of Apothic, some time on raids raising faction with the quest mob, and a long raid to get to clear the zone and go to the second floor where the quest is done. I actually would do this quest three times; once to get the epic staff, a second time to get back my good armor, and a third time to get back the earth staff (PLZ remember it is a useful mage item IN AND OF ITSELF and OMFG I'm not going to try to get a second one the way things are right now).<br>
2.) Make Magi more common.<br>
3.) Make Magi drop multiple copies of the staff.<br>
4.) Consider adding epic drops to Haunted Chests but make them uncommon or rare. This would ensure that ON EVERY raid there is the at least the possibility of getting a staff even if it's very slim. I'd then have at least hope with me on every raid and it'd be more exciting. That'd be better than going LFG, getting a group for Hate and committing the next 4-6 hours for the raid (because leaving a raid early on a regular basis is bad form), and then finding out from some ranger or monk that the mob you went up there for isn't there. That's a REAL DOWNER!! There's no decent exp on a Hate raid, no loot after your first ten raids; so you basically spend time for nothing in most cases. It's pretty depressing.<br>
<br>
Verant should also consider the potential that as the game matures, more and more people will be completing different parts of their epic (as I have) and will eventually be down to their last piece (usually Hate staff, Air Crown, and Quillmane cloak in that order). The bottleneck could only get worse in time.<br>
<br>
Please consider all that I've said (I really hope it's read - it at least means something to me) and maybe respond or make a change that could benefit everyone.<br>
<br>
Thanks again for all the good times (and I guess the bad ones too hehe).<br>
<br>
- Caeadyen<br>
Lvl 57 Tunare Magician<br>
